Defendant Robert L Harris in court with attorney Colin P. McGinn.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1:  Court sentenced defendant to serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence.  Court ordered the defendant to pay a fine of $25.00 including costs to be paid by 05-20-2016 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 MONTHS  in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS CONSECUTIVE to any other term of probation.
Conditions:  
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $1300.00 to Lucinda S. or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment; order, signed and filed;
*  Write a letter of apology to Lucinda S.;
*  Perform no loan modification work;
*  Perform 25 hours of community service;
*  Court will waive all costs and surcharges that can be waived.  Any costs and surcharges that can not be waived are to be paid during the term of probation.
  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
